📌 What is Auto Scaling Group (ASG)?
        ASG (Auto Scaling Group) is an AWS service that automatically launches or terminates EC2 instances based on demand 
      — ensuring your application always has the right number of instances running at the right time.

🖥️ Part 1 — Create Launch Template:
Step 1 — Navigate:

Go to AWS Console → EC2
In the left panel → Click "Launch Templates"
Click "Create Launch Template"
Step 2 — Configure Launch Template:

Table


Setting	Value
Launch Template Name	demo-lt
Description	Launch Template for ASG Demo
OS / AMI	Amazon Linux 2
Instance Type	t2.micro(Free Tier)
Key Pair	EC2 Tutorial1
Security Group	launch-wizard-1
⚠️ Correction: You wrote demo-tg as the launch template name — but demo-tg is already used for the Target Group. Use demo-lt to avoid confusion.

Step 3 — Add User Data (Bootstrap Script):

Expand "Advanced Details"
Scroll down to "User Data"
Paste the following:

Copy
bash
#!/bin/bash
# Use this for your user data (script from top to bottom)
# Install httpd (Amazon Linux 2 version)
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Hello World from $(hostname -f)</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
Click "Create Launch Template" ✅
